{"id":"aha","term":"Aha!","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>An exclamation of ridicule (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 35:21\">Ps. 35:21</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 40:15\">40:15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 70:3\">70:3</a>). In <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 44:16\">Isa. 44:16</a> it signifies joyful surprise, as also in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Job 39:25\">Job 39:25</a>, R.V.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Psalms 35:21","Psalms 40:15","Psalms 70:3","Isaiah 44:16","Job 39:25"]}